The following code does not compile in iverilog.  I believe this is valid systemVerilog code.  At least one commercial tool accepts this happily.  iverilog seems to be unhappy about the datatype and wants a cast.

-------------------------------------
module enumtestcase();

typedef enum {
   		STATE_A,
   		STATE_B
	     } t_STATE ;
			 
wire mywire;  //not set just defined to illustrate error


t_STATE state;
t_STATE nxt_state;


always_comb
  case(state)
    STATE_A  : nxt_state = mywire ? STATE_B : STATE_A;  //this line is invalid in iverilog
  endcase

endmodule
----------------------------

I compiled with:
iverilog -g2012 enumtestcase.v

The error was:

enumtestcase.v:17: error: This assignment requires an explicit cast.
